# MCP Tools Rules - ArchivistMCP

## Tool Definition

```kotlin
server.addTool(
    name = "index_document",
    description = "Indexes a document for semantic search"
) { request ->
    // request is a typed data class
}
```

## Tool Naming

- Use `snake_case` for tool names
- Examples: `index_document`, `query_documents`, `list_documents`, `delete_document`

## Result Types

```kotlin
// Use CallToolResult with TextContent
CallToolResult(
    content = listOf(TextContent("Success: document indexed"))
)

// JSON structure for complex results
CallToolResult(
    content = listOf(TextContent(
        """{"documentId": "abc123", "chunks": 5}"""
    ))
)
```

## Arguments

Type arguments via data classes:

```kotlin
data class IndexDocumentRequest(
    val path: String,
    val collection: String = "documents"
)

server.addTool<IndexDocumentRequest, CallToolResult>(
    name = "index_document",
    description = "Indexes a document"
) { request ->
    // request.path, request.collection available
}
```

## Resources

```kotlin
server.addResource(
    uri = "file://{path}",
    name = "Document",
    description = "Access to document",
    mimeType = "text/plain"
) { request ->
    ReadResourceResult(
        contents = listOf(TextResourceContents(content, request.uri, "text/plain"))
    )
}
```

## Prompts

```kotlin
server.addPrompt(
    name = "document_search",
    description = "Search documents by query",
    arguments = listOf(
        PromptArgument(name = "query", description = "Search query", required = true)
    )
) { request ->
    GetPromptResult(
        messages = listOf(
            PromptMessage(
                role = Role.User,
                content = TextContent("Find documents: ${request.arguments?.get("query")}")
            )
        )
    )
}
```

## Transport

- **STDIO**: `runMcpServerUsingStdio()` — for local agents
- **SSE**: `runSseMcpServerUsingKtorPlugin(port)` — for HTTP connections
- Endpoint: `/sse` + `/message`

## Server Capabilities

```kotlin
ServerOptions(
    capabilities = ServerCapabilities(
        prompts = ServerCapabilities.Prompts(listChanged = true),
        resources = ServerCapabilities.Resources(subscribe = true, listChanged = true),
        tools = ServerCapabilities.Tools(listChanged = true),
    ),
)